    {
      "level": "C",
      "levelType": "major",
      "text": "The reproductive system in plants: its organization and function",
      "children": [
        {
          "level": "1",
          "levelType": "numeric",
          "text": "General features: asexual systems that create new plants identical to the parent plant, sexual systems that create new plants different from either of the two parents",
